        <hl1>George Divoky's Planet</hl1>
      </hedline>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Frey's artful account recalls, in the language of its chapter headings, Coleridge's poem ''The Rime of the Ancient Mariner.'' Divoky's courageous career, Frey's powerful retelling of it and the Coleridge poem seem to converge and offer hope that art, science and spirit will in time defeat the one enemy that is greater than global warming. Namely, our denial of it.</p>
        <p>Alfred M. Niese Jr.  Woolwich, Me.</p>
      </block>
